# kmp-contact Overview

- This is a multi-module Kotlin Multiplatform project with shared modules in `kmp/` and platform modules in `android/`, `web/`, and `ios/`.
- Preserve dependency direction: platform modules depend on shared modules, `kmp/data` depends on `kmp/domain`, and `kmp/support` depends on `kmp/domain`.
- Keep `commonMain` platform-agnostic. Do not introduce Android, browser, or iOS-specific APIs into shared code.
- Make changes in the narrowest layer that owns the behavior instead of patching around it from UI code.
- Treat `kmp/data` as the owner of repository orchestration, DTO/entity mapping, request payloads, cache writes, and network fallback behavior.
- Android uses Hilt for DI; Web uses manual wiring in `web/contacts/.../main.kt`; the repo only contains an iOS helper module, not a full iOS app shell.
- Do not turn current local WIP into a permanent project convention unless the task explicitly requires it.
